phasis of legal protections and behavioral conditioning of poor parents to accommodate employers. Ridzi draws a compelling portrait of how welfare staff and their clients negotiate the complexities of the low wage labor market in an age of global competition, exposing the realities of how the new "common sense" of poverty is affecting the lives of poor and vulnerable Americans.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPoorxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aPublic welfarezUnited States. 0aWelfare recipientsxEmploymentxGovernment policyzUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh  aAmericans.  aRidzi.  aaffecting.  aclients.  acommon.  acompelling.  acompetition.  acomplexities.  adraws.  aexposing.  aglobal.  alabor.  alives.  amarket.  anegotiate.  apoor.  aportrait.  apoverty.  arealities.  asense.  astaff.  atheir.  avulnerable.  awage.  awelfare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081477593640uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814775936.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814777374423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814777374/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK